The paper deals with probabilistic queries on trajectory databases, which are typically studied in the context of data management (cs.DB). The use of stochastic processes and Bayesian inference suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.AI) and statistical inference (cs.LG). The paper also proposes algorithms for query evaluation, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the experimental study involves simulations and performance evaluation, which could be considered as part of scientific computing (cs.SI).
